Description: Corroded copper alloy amuletic figure, small and roughly made, of a seated ape.
Curator's comments: The Museum register indicates a general reference to the small bronze finds mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 80 § 80, where the item seems not clearly described (possibly one of the "sacred animals"?).
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 80 § 80) (?)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.45, p.48, p.49, p.63, p.180, pl.22)
